      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AQUEDUCT (1) is flying and looks hard to beat again. He's won two on the bounce, getting up by a long neck at Ballarat last time in a good race. Big weight but Olivia East is a capable apprentice who takes off 3kg and can get the job done. BLETHYN (2) struggled last time in stronger company at Morphettville. He won two on the bounce prior and will be hard to hold out. DAPPER DARRI (3) ran on well fresh at Sale to get within a length. He can come on from that and go one better. BLACKBERRY BOMB (4) has been below her best in recent times. She flies second up, expect sharp improvement. POCKET SIZE (9) could be an improver third up.",
